## Explore tab — jobs, skills, connections, DMs

### How the feature works

- **Jobs** and **skill listings** live in Firestore `expansion_jobs` and `expansion_skills` ([explore_listings_repository.dart](lib/services/explore_listings_repository.dart)). Fields include **`skill_seeking`** (job — array of 1–30 labels from the curriculum list in [curriculum_onboarding_data.dart](lib/data/curriculum_onboarding_data.dart)), **`skill_offering`** (skill listing — same), **`industry`** (dropdown from [explore_posting_industries.dart](lib/data/explore_posting_industries.dart), includes **Technology**), **`location_mode`** (`remote` \| `in_person`), and **`location`** (stored as `Remote` or city/state text; **In person** prefills from `users/{uid}` **`city`** + **`state`** via `UserProfileRepository.getCityStateLineForUser`). Legacy docs may store a single string for `skill_seeking` / `skill_offering`; the app maps that to a one-element list. Explore cards and home **Latest job/skill** rows join selected skills with ` · `. Explore shows filters **All / Jobs / Skills / Connections**; **Connections** remains sample rows with chat to `/messages/direct/{userId}`.
- **Post flows:** FAB **+** → bottom sheet: **Post a job** (`/explore/jobs/create` — onboarding-style **Skills seeking** multiselect via [ExploreCurriculumSkillsMultiselect](lib/widgets/explore_curriculum_skills_multiselect.dart) + title, industry, location mode, optional company/description), **Offer a skill** (`/explore/skills/create` — **Skills offering** multiselect + headline, industry, location, summary). No separate **Skills hub** entry from Explore (full list still at `/explore/skills` if linked elsewhere).
- **Dev seed (fixed fixtures):** `infra/scripts/seed-expansion-stage-mock.js` (npm `seed:dev:expansion-mock` / `seed:stage:expansion-mock`) creates Auth + `users/` for emails **`seed.mock.u0@mortar-dev.local`** through **`seed.mock.u19@mortar-dev.local`**, `expansion_jobs` with **`skill_seeking`** = merged **preferred + growth** skills from the embedded job list, `expansion_skills` **only for `skill_type: offering` rows** with **`skill_offering`** = `[skill_title]` (headline text), five **`events_mobile`** docs, and five **`groups_mobile`** communities each with one welcome thread and five seeded comments. No scaling flags; edit **`RAW_*`** arrays in that file to change data. **`CRM systems`** in job skill lists is normalized to the full curriculum CRM label on write. **Auth for the script:** use **`--credentials path/to/adminsdk.json`** (Firebase Console → Project settings → Service accounts) or **`GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`**; **`mortar-stage`** needs a key for that project (do not commit keys). **`gcloud auth application-default login`** also works if the Cloud SDK is installed.
- **Profile avatars on listings:** [PosterProfileAvatar](lib/widgets/poster_profile_avatar.dart) on job/skill cards and in **Direct chat** (header + message rows); **Messages** list avatars open the peer’s profile modal.
- **Messaging about a listing:** **Message** on a job or skill card opens `/messages/direct/{authorId}?attach=job&id={jobId}` or `attach=skill&id={skillId}`. [DirectChatScreen](lib/screens/direct_chat_screen.dart) shows a pending attachment strip; the first send includes `attachment_type` / `attachment_id` on the message doc. [MessagingAttachmentPreview](lib/widgets/messaging_attachment_preview.dart) renders the card above the text in the thread.
- **Direct messages:** `dm_threads/{uidSmall_uidLarge}` with `participant_ids` (sorted), `updated_at`, `last_preview`, `last_sender_id`. Messages in `dm_threads/{id}/messages/{msgId}` with `sender_id`, `text`, `created_at`, optional attachment fields. [MessagesScreen](lib/screens/messages_screen.dart) lists threads for the current user (`array-contains` + `orderBy updated_at` — composite index in `firestore.indexes.json`).

