## Groups tab — Reddit-style threads (Firestore)

### How the feature works

- **List (`GroupsScreen`):** Streams **`groups_mobile`**. Layout: **Your groups** (member), **Featured communities** (star header + horizontal cards — **top two groups by activity**: `lastActivityAt`, then `threadCount`, then `memberCount`; not `isFeatured` flags), **Explore** (not a member). Subtitle explains communities ≈ subreddits and posts ≈ threads. Header **+** goes to [group_create_screen.dart](lib/screens/group_create_screen.dart) (`/groups/create`). Search filters name, `category`, and description.
- **Categories:** Fixed allowlist in [group_categories.dart](lib/data/group_categories.dart). Create and edit use a **dropdown**; values are stored on the group doc as **`category`** (camelCase). Firestore rules enforce the same allowlist when `category` is present.
- **Detail (`GroupDetailScreen`):** Streams **`groups_mobile/{groupId}`** and paginated **`threads`** (15 per page). **Top app bar** is only **back + community name + edit** (for managers) — it is not styled like a thread. **Threads tab:** a **Community** card first (category, about, member/thread counts, open/closed), then a **Threads** section with sort **New / Top / Helpful** and **individual thread cards** ([FirestoreThreadTile](lib/widgets/group_thread/firestore_thread_tile.dart) `GroupThreadTileVariant.listPreview`: rounded bordered cards). **Tap a card** (or chevron) opens a **bottom sheet** with full post + [GroupCommentTree](lib/widgets/group_thread/group_comment_tree.dart) (`showGroupThreadDetailSheet` / `fullDetail`). **Tap the author row** on a card to open **`showUserProfileModal`**. **Members tab:** each member row is tappable for the same profile modal; **Message** still goes to `/messages/direct/{userId}`. **Join** / **Leave** use **`joinGroup` / `leaveGroup`** with `scope: "mobile"`. **+** opens **New thread** (`createThread`).
- **Edit / delete:** **`/groups/:groupId/edit`** ([group_edit_screen.dart](lib/screens/group_edit_screen.dart)) for **creator** (`createdBy`) or **staff** (Auth token `roles` includes `Admin` or `superAdmin`, same as `firestore.rules` `hasStaffClaim()`). Saves **name**, **category**, **about**, **rules**, **Open/Closed** via `GroupThreadRepository.updateGroupMetadata`. **Delete** calls Cloud Function **`deleteMobileGroup`**, which removes the group doc and all **`threads`**, **`comments`**, and **`votes`** (client-only parent delete would orphan subcollections).
- **Legacy web chat:** Digital Curriculum still uses **`Groups/.../Messages`** for linear chat; mobile threads live under **`threads`** (same security model: members-only).
- **Badges / gamification:** Cloud Functions maintain **`users/{uid}.gamification.counters`** (`posts_created`, `comments_created`) and may append **`badges.earned`** when thresholds in **`badge_definitions`** `criteria` are met. Profile shows optional **`badges.featured_badge_id`** and a **View achievements** link to `/profile/achievements` ([AchievementsScreen](lib/screens/achievements_screen.dart)). Owners may change `badges.visible` / `featured_badge_id` but **not** `badges.earned` or `gamification` (see `firestore.rules`).
- **Admin seed (console):** Example `badge_definitions` doc id `first_post`: `{ "name": "Conversation starter", "description": "Created your first group post", "display_order": 0, "tier": "standard", "criteria": { "min_posts_created": 1 } }`.

## Security rules note

See repo root `firestore.rules` — shared with Digital Curriculum. **`events`**: reads respect **`approval_status`** (pending/rejected visible to submitter + staff; approved or legacy docs to all signed-in users). Members may **create** pending events with a fixed allowlist of fields; **RSVP** updates only when the event is published. Curriculum **`Groups`**: document updates **staff-only**; threads/messages rules unchanged. Expansion **`groups_mobile`**: any signed-in user may **create** a group (with `createdBy`, self in `GroupMembers`); optional **`category`** must match the app allowlist when set; **creator** may edit metadata (including **`Status`**) but not membership arrays or counters (join/leave still via **`joinGroup` / `leaveGroup`** with `scope: "mobile"`). **Staff** token roles may edit/delete groups; **deep delete** for subcollections is done by **`deleteMobileGroup`**, not only `delete` on the group doc. **`groups_mobile/.../threads`**, **`comments`**, **`votes`** mirror `Groups` and use **`isMobileGroupMember`**. **`expansion_jobs`** / **`expansion_skills`**: signed-in read; create with **`author_id`** = self and allowlisted keys; author update/delete cannot change **`author_id`**. **`dm_threads`** and **`dm_threads/.../messages`**: participants only; thread id must match sorted `participant_ids`. **`users/{uid}`**: owners cannot change **`gamification`** or **`badges.earned`**. **`badge_definitions`** read if signed-in; write staff. **`achievement_events`** client writes denied.

`eligibleUsers` / `inviteCodes` remain function-gated for writes. Details: `EXPANSION_INVITE_AUTH.md`.

## Development: Hot Restart vs Firebase (Android)

If you see:

`PlatformException(channel-error, Unable to establish connection on channel: ... FirebaseCoreHostApi.initializeCore ...)`

that usually happens after **Hot Restart**. Stop the app completely, then **Run** again (cold start). Prefer **Hot Reload** for UI work.

The same **Pigeon channel** break can appear when calling **Cloud Functions** (e.g. `validateInviteCode`, `initializeUserSession`):

`Unable to establish connection on channel: '...CloudFunctionsHostApi.call'`

That is **not** a bad invite or “stranger” flow logic — the Dart ↔ Android **MethodChannel** for `cloud_functions` is broken. Typical causes:

1. **Hot Restart (`R`)** on Android after Firebase/plugins loaded — use **Hot Reload (`r`)** only, or fully **stop** the app and **Run** again.
2. **APK never rebuilt** after adding `cloud_functions` — run **`flutter clean`**, **`flutter pub get`**, uninstall the app from the device/emulator, then **Run** so native `cloud_functions` code is packaged.
3. Rare emulator glitches — cold-boot the AVD or use a physical device.

Claim/sign-in screens map this to a short message via `userMessageForFirebaseCallableError` in `expansion_session_service.dart` (detection includes `cloud_functions_platform_interface` / `unknown` callable errors).

`lib/main.dart` skips `Firebase.initializeApp` when `Firebase.apps` is already populated, and logs a hint if init fails.
